-- Bugs Fixed and Ready For Release 
Fixed: Shields obscure health bars
Fixed: Napalm does not now work under water (I'll not change this again ;) )
Fixed: Camera does not follow meteors or other environment actions
Fixed: Talk text appears under other windows (text now smaller too)
Fixed: Fix camera presets
Fixed: CTRL LF in mod files linux hosts causing mod file downloads
Fixed: New games or rounds do not cause mod downloads to stop
Fixed: Reduced the server to client payload size considerably (lag??)
Fixed: Key repeat for console macros bound to keys
Fixed: wx 2.5 compilation errors (sizers still to fix)
Fixed: Tank name is above ground when tank burried
Fixed: Accessories.xml file format to remove duplication
Fixed: Computer AIs becoming confused when shots hit off walls
Fixed: Aming sight is correctly positioned for all tanks
Fixed: Bug where a player is assigned black as their color

Added: flame color attributes to WeaponProjectile to control the trail color
Added: smokelife and flamelife attributes to WeaponProjectile to control trail length
Added: nosmoke and noobjectdamage attributes to WeaponNapalm to control smoke and tree damage
Added: Player decals stored in database for stats usage
Added: Optional Armslevel attribute to weapons (if missing parents armslevel is used)
Added: Player and weapon icons to game gui
Added: Mods in the users mod directory are moved out the way when a new version is installed
Added: Each computer AI can now have multiple different buying stratagies
Added: New aiming algorithm for Cyborg computer AI (copes with wind and tank movement)
Added: Computer AIs now choose weapons more appropraitely
Added: Maximum number of weapons can be set on a per weapon basis
Added: Starting number of weapons can be set on a per weapon basis
Added: Start timer to server for joining players
Added: Player decals for in game
Added: Banned username and time to players that have been banned
Added: Users can turn IP authentication off
Added: Weapon and talk icons to the speach lines
Added: Mod file import and export in options dialog

